{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"df1991e6-e779-40fc-80cc-fd86587e3032","content":"","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_ekDy9nhVu7459Dpz4gKyyv","name":"view","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-bb30ed63cba0460ab2e414ac6be42de9/.template.config"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"view the file at /tmp/sv-bb30ed63cba0460ab2e414ac6be42de9/.template.config."},{"toolCallId":"tooluse_fwYXX5cZp91LElel3LjhuD","name":"view","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-bb30ed63cba0460ab2e414ac6be42de9"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"view the file at /tmp/sv-bb30ed63cba0460ab2e414ac6be42de9."}],"interactionId":"6695e721-f13b-4a1d-b526-63a28a79ba9b","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Let me review this template.json for NuGet publishing readiness. I'll check against the .NET template engine schema requirements.\n\nIssues I see:\n\n1. **Missing `$schema`** — Not strictly required, but strongly recommended for validation and editor support. Should be `\"$schema\": \"http://json.schemastore.org/template\"`.\n\n2. **Missing `groupIdentity`** — Recommended for NuGet packages so templates can be grouped/updated properly.\n\n3. **Missing `precedence`** — Useful when multiple versions of the same template are installed.\n\n4. **Missing `preferNameDirectory`** — Minor, but good practice for project templates.\n\n\n5. **The `Framework` symbol isn't wired to the project file** — It's defined but lacks a `replaces` property to actually inject the framework choice into the target files, so selecting a framework won't have any effect.\n\n6. **No `defaultName`** — Users running `dotnet new mywebapi` without specifying `-n` will get a generic fallback name instead of something sensible.\n\nLet me check what other files are in this directory.","outputTokens":412},"id":"a680d0be-b141-435e-89b4-16fc57354252","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:43:58.600Z","parentId":"6a34e1ed-1d84-440e-875f-9e891acceac4"}
